obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6873)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 20th February, 2009, vide notification No. S.O. 517(E), dated 20th February, 2009, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II sec.3(ii)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6873&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Assam Rifles Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6874)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6874&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "active duty", in relation to a person subject to this Act, means any duty as a member of the`
  line `Force during the period in which such person is attached to, or forms part of, a unit of the Force—`
  line
  line `(i) which is engaged in operations against an enemy or an insurgent or a terrorist or any`
  line `person in arms against the Union, or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is operating at a picket or engaged on patrol or other guard duty along the borders`
  line `of India,`
  line
  line `and includes duty by such person during any period declared by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, as a period of active duty with reference to any area in which or`
  line `under any provision of this Act or for the purposes of any other law for the time being in force, any`
  line `person or class of persons subject to this Act may be serving;`
  line
  line `(b) "Assam Rifles Court" means a Court referred to in section 86;`
  line
  line `(c) "battalion" means a unit of the Force constituted as battalion by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) "Chief Law Officer" and "Law Officer" mean, respectively, the Chief Law Officer and a Law`
  line `Officer of the Force appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) "civil offence" means as offence which is triable by a criminal court;`
  line
  line `(f) "civil prison" means any jail or place used for the detention of any criminal prisoner under the`
  line `Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894) or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(g) "Commandant", when used in any provision of this Act with reference to any unit of the`
  line `Force, means the officer whose duty it is under the rules or regulations or in the absence of such rules`
  line `or regulations, by custom of the service, to discharge with respect to that unit, the functions of a`
  line `Commandant in regard to matters of the description referred to in that provision;`
  line
  line `(h) "criminal court" means a court of ordinary criminal justice in any part of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "deputation" means a period for which the services of a person belonging to any department of`
  line `the Central Government are placed at the disposal of the Director-General;`
  line
  line `(j) "Director-General" and "Additional Director-General" mean, the Director-General and`
  line `Additional Director-General of the Force appointed under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 5,`
  line respectively;
  line
  line `(k) "enemy" includes all armed mutineers, armed rebels, armed rioters, pirates, terrorists and any`
  line `person in arms against whom it is the duty of any person subject to this Act to take action;`
  line
  line `(l) "enrolled person" means an under-officer or other person enrolled under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "Force" means the Assam Rifles;`
  line
  line `(n) "Force custody" means the arrest or confinement of a member of the Force according to rules`
  line `and includes any military custody of such member under the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(o) "Inspector-General" and "Deputy Inspector-General" mean, respectively the InspectorGeneral`
  line `and the Deputy Inspector-General of the Force appointed under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(p) "member of the Force" means an officer, a subordinate officer, an under-officer or other`
  line `enrolled person and includes the persons on deputation;`
  line
  line `(q) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(r) "offence" means any act or omission punishable under this Act and includes a civil offence;`
  line
  line `(s) "officer" means a person appointed or in pay as an officer of the Force; but does not include a`
  line `subordinate officer or an under-officer;`
  line
  line `(t) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(u) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) "rule" means a rule made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(w) "subordinate officer" means a person appointed or in pay as a Subedar Major, a Subedar or a`
  line `Naib Subedar of the Force;`
  line
  line `(x) "superior officer", when used in relation to a person subject to this Act, means—`
  line
  line `(i) any member of the Force or a person on deputation to whose command such person is for`
  line `the time being subject in accordance with the rules;`
  line
  line `(ii) any officer of higher rank or class or of a higher grade in the same class,`
  line `and includes when such person is not an officer, a subordinate officer or an under-officer of higher`
  line `rank, class or grade;`
  line
  line `(y) "terrorist" means any person who, with intent to overawe the Government as by law`
  line `established or to strike terror in the people or any section of the people or to alienate any section of`
  line `the people or to adversely affect the harmony amongst different sections of the people, does any act`
  line `or thing by using bombs, dynamite or other explosive substances or inflammable substances or firearms`
  line `or other lethal weapons or poisons or noxious gases or other chemicals or any other substances`
  line `(whether biological or otherwise) of a hazardous nature in such a manner, as to cause or is likely to`
  line `cause death of, or injury to, any person or persons, or damage to, or destruction of, property or`
  line `disruption of any supplies or services essential to the life of the community;`
  line
  line `(z) "under-officer" means a Warrant Officer, Havildar, Naik and Lance Naik of the Force;`
  line
  line `(za) "unit" means any—`
  line
  line `(i) battalion; or`
  line
  line `(ii) regiment; or`
  line
  line `(iii) training institution; or`
  line
  line `(iv) Head Quarters of Deputy Inspector-General; or`
  line
  line `(v) Head Quarters of Inspector-General; or`
  line
  line `(vi) Head Quarters of Director-General,`
  line
  line `of the Force and includes any other formation of the Force specified, by notification by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Penal Code (45`
  line `of 1860) shall have the meanings assigned to them in that Code.`
  line
  line `(3) In this Act, reference to any law not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir shall be`
  line `construed as references to the corresponding law in force in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6875)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Persons subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6875&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons (whether on deputation or otherwise`
  line `employed) shall be subject to this Act, wherever they may be, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) officers and subordinate officers; and`
  line
  line `(b) under-officers and other persons enrolled under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Members of the Force in existence at the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed or, as the case may be, enrolled as such under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any person who is employed in the Force`
  line `on deputation from the regular Army as defined under clause (xxi) of section 3 of the Army Act, 1950 (46`
  line `of 1950) shall not be subject to this Act and shall, during the period of such deputation, be deemed to be`
  line `subject to the Army Act, 1950:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person in regard to his duties and discipline shall be deemed to be under the`
  line `command of the member of the Force under whose command such person for the time being is placed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in case of such person, for the purposes of his duties and discipline, the`
  line `expression "active duty" defined in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 2 shall be deemed to be the`
  line `"active service" as defined in clause (i) of section 3 of the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950) for taking any`
  line `action against him under the provisions of the said Army Act,`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who is not subject to this Act is posted for any service with the members of the Force`
  line `or engaged to accompany with or to provide any service in any manner to the members of the Force in`
  line such—
  line
  line `(i) camp;`
  line
  line `(ii) line of march;`
  line
  line `(iii) frontier post;`
  line
  line `(iv) active duty ;or`
  line
  line `(v) counter insurgency operations,`
  line
  line `as may be specified, by notification, by the Central Government in this behalf shall be deemed to be a`
  line `member of the Force, till he is so posted or engaged in such corresponding rank as may be determined, by`
  line `notification, by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Every person subject to this Act shall remain so subject until retired, discharged, released,`
  line `removed or dismissed from the Force in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6876)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6876&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an armed force of the Union called the Assam Rifles`
  line `for ensuring the security of the borders of India, to carry out counter insurgency operations in the`
  line `specified areas and to act in aid of civil authorities for the maintenance of law and order and the matters`
  line `connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Force shall be reconstituted in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and the conditions of service of the members of the Force shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6877)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Control, direction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6877&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and control of the Force shall`
  line `vest in, and be exercised by, the Central Government and subject thereto and to the provisions of this Act`
  line `and the rules and regulations, the command and supervision of the Force shall vest in an officer to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government as the Director-General of the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General shall, in the discharge of his duties under this Act, be assisted by such`
  line `number of Additional Director-General, Inspectors-General, Deputy Inspectors-General, Commandants`
  line `and other officers as may be appointed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6878)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Enrolment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6878&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons to be enrolled to the Force, the mode of enrolment and the procedure`
  line `for enrolment shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the rules and regulations, every person who`
  line `has, for a continuous period of three months, been in receipt of pay as a person enrolled under this Act`
  line `and borne on the rolls of the Force shall be deemed to have been duly enrolled.`
  line
  line `(3) No person who is not a citizen of India shall, except by the consent of the Central Government`
  line `signified in writing, be enrolled in the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6879)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability for service outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6879&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Force shall be liable to serve in any`
  line `part of India as well as outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6880)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Resignation and withdrawal from the post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6880&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No member of the Force shall be at liberty—`
  line
  line `(a) to resign his appointment during the term of his engagement ;or`
  line
  line `(b) to withdraw himself from all or any of the duties of his appointment,`
  line
  line `except with the previous permission in writing of the prescribed authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6881)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Tenure of service under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6881&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every person subject to this Act shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6882)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Termination of service by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6882&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules and regulations, the Central Government may dismiss or remove from the service any person subject`
  line `to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6883)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Dismissal, removal or reduction by Director-General and by other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6883&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Director-General, Additional Director-General or any Inspector-General may dismiss or remove from`
  line `service or reduce to a lower grade or rank or the ranks any person subject to this Act other than an officer.`
  line
  line `(2) An officer not below the rank of Deputy Inspector-General may dismiss or remove from the`
  line `service any person under his command other than an officer or a subordinate officer of such rank or the`
  line `ranks as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such officer as is mentioned in sub-section (2) may reduce to a lower grade or rank or the`
  line `ranks any person under his command except an officer or a subordinate officer.`
  line
  line `(4) The exercise of any power under this section shall be subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules and regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6884)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Certificate of termination of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6884&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A subordinate officer or an under-officer or other`
  line `enrolled person who is retired, discharged, released, removed or dismissed from service shall be furnished`
  line `by the officer, to whose command he is subject, with a certificate in the language which is the mothertongue`
  line `of such person and also in Hindi and English language setting forth—`
  line
  line `(a) the authority terminating his service;`
  line
  line `(b) the cause for such termination; and`
  line
  line `(c) the full period of his service in the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6885)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Restrictions on right to form association, freedom of speech, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6885&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person subject to`
  line `this Act shall, without the previous sanction in writing of the Central Government or of the prescribed`
  line authority,—
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not recognised as part of the Force or is not of a purely social, recreational or`
  line `religious nature ; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or organisation`
  line `is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section, the decision of`
  line `the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No person subject to this Act shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by any body or persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6886)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Authorised deduction only to be made from pay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6886&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The pay of every person subject to this Act`
  line `due to him as such under any rules or regulations for the time being in force shall be paid without any`
  line `deduction other than the deductions authorised by or under this Act or any other Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6887)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Remedy of aggrieved persons other than officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6887&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act other`
  line `than an officer who deems himself wronged by any officer or subordinate officer may complain to the`
  line `officer under whose command or orders he is serving.`
  line
  line `(2) when the officer complained against is the officer to whom any complaint should, under`
  line `sub-section (1), be preferred, the aggrieved person may complain to such officer's next superior officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer receiving any such complaint shall make as complete an investigation into it as may`
  line `be possible for giving full redress to the complainant; or when necessary, refer the complaint to superior`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(4) Every such complaint shall be preferred in such manner as may, from time to time, be specified by`
  line `the Director-General.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may revise any decision by the Director-General under sub-section (2),`
  line `but, subject thereto, the decision of the Director-General shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6888)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Remedy of aggrieved officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6888&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any officer who deems himself wronged by his Commandant`
  line `or any superior officer and who on due application made to his Commandant or such superior officer does`
  line `not receive the redress to which he considers himself entitled, may complain to the Central Government`
  line `in such manner as may, from time to time, be specified by the Director-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6889)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Immunity from attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6889&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Neither the arms, clothes, equipment, accoutrements or`
  line `necessaries of any person subject to this Act, nor any animal used by him for the discharge of his duty`
  line `shall be seized, nor shall, the pay and allowances of any such person or any part thereof, be attached by`
  line `direction of any civil or revenue court or any revenue officer in satisfaction of any decree or order`
  line `enforceable against him.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6890)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Immunity from arrest for debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6890&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person subject to this Act shall, so long as he belongs`
  line `to the Force, be liable to be arrested for debt under any process issued by, or by the authority of, any civil`
  line `or revenue court or revenue officer, except with the prior consent of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judge of any such court or the said officer may examine into any complaint made by such`
  line `person or his superior officer of the arrest of such person contrary to the provisions of this section and`
  line `may, by warrant under his hand, discharge the person, and award reasonable costs to the complainant,`
  line `who may recover those costs in like manner as he might have recovered costs awarded to him by a decree`
  line `against the person obtaining the process.`
  line
  line `(3) For the recovery of such costs no court-fee shall be payable by the complainant`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (6891)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Immunity of persons attending Assam Rifles Court from arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6891&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Presiding Officer or`
  line `member of an Assam Rifles Court, no Law Officer, no party to any proceeding before an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court, or his legal practitioner or agent and no witness acting in obedience to a summons to attend an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court shall, while proceeding to, attending or returning from, an Assam Rifles Court, be`
  line `liable to arrest under civil or revenue process.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such person is arrested under any such process, he may be discharged by order of the`
  line `Assam Rifles Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (6892)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Saving of rights and privileges under other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6892&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The rights and privileges specified in the`
  line `preceding section of this Chapter shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other rights and`
  line `privileges conferred on persons subject to this Act generally by any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (6893)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Offences in relation to the enemy and punishable with death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6893&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act`
  line `who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) shamefully abandons or delivers up any post, place or guard, committed to his charge or`
  line `which it is his duty to defend; or`
  line
  line `(b) intentionally uses any means to compel or induce any person subject to this Act or to army,`
  line `naval, air force law or any member of other armed forces to abstain from acting against the enemy or`
  line `to discourage such person from acting against the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the presence of enemy, shamefully casts away his arms, ammunition, tools or equipment or`
  line `misbehaves in such manner as to show cowardice; or`
  line
  line `(d) treacherously holds correspondence with, or communicates intelligence to, the enemy or any`
  line `person in arms against the Union; or`
  line
  line `(e) directly or indirectly assists the enemy with money, arms, ammunition, stores or supplies or in`
  line `any other manner whatsoever; or`
  line
  line `(f) in time of active operation against the enemy intentionally occasions a false alarm in action,`
  line `camp, quarters or spreads or causes to be spread reports calculated to create alarm or despondency; or`
  line
  line `(g) in time of action leaves his Commandant or other superior officer or his post, guard, picket,`
  line `patrol or party wihout being regularly relieved or without leave; or`
  line
  line `(h) having been captured by the enemy or made a prisoner of war, voluntarily serves with or aids`
  line `the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(i) knowingly harbours or protects an enemy not being a prisoner; or`
  line
  line `(j) being a sentry in time of active operation against the enemy or alarm, sleeps upon his post or is`
  line `intoxicated; or`
  line
  line `(k) knowingly does any act calculated to imperil the success of the Force or the army, naval, air`
  line `forces of India or any other armed forces of the Central Government co-operating therewith or any`
  line `part of such forces,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer death or such less punishment as is in`
  line `this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (6894)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Offences in relation to the enemy and not punishable with death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6894&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) is taken prisoner or captured by the enemy, by want of due precaution or through`
  line `disobedience of orders, or wilful neglect of duty, or having been taken prisoner or so captured fails to`
  line `rejoin his service when able to do so; or`
  line
  line `(b) without due authority holds correspondence with, or communicates intelligence to, the enemy`
  line `or any person in league with the enemy or having come by the knowledge of any such`
  line `correspondence or communication, wilfully omits to discover it immediately to his Commandant or`
  line `other superior officer,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (6895)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Offences punishable more severely on active duty than at other times.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6895&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to`
  line `this Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) forces a safeguard or forces or uses criminal force to a sentry; or`
  line
  line `(b) breaks into any house or other place in search of plunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) being a sentry, sleeps upon his post or is intoxicated; or`
  line
  line `(d) without orders from his superior officer, leaves his guard, picket, patrol or posts; or`
  line
  line `(e) intentionally or through neglect occasions a false alarm in camp or quarters, or spreads or`
  line `causes to be spread reports calculated to create unnecessary alarm or despondency; or`
  line
  line `(f) makes known the parole, watchword or countersign to any person not entitled to receive it ;or`
  line
  line `(g) knowingly gives a parole, watchword or countersign different from what he received,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court,—`
  line
  line `(A) if he commits any such offence when on active duty, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(B) if he commits any such offence when not on active duty, be liable to suffer imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (6896)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Mutiny.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6896&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to`
  line say,—
  line
  line `(a) begins, incites, causes or conspires with any other person to cause any mutiny in the Force or`
  line `in the army, naval or air forces of India or any forces co-operating therewith; or`
  line
  line `(b) joins in any such mutiny; or`
  line
  line `(c) being present at any such mutiny, does not use his utmost endeavours to suppress the same; or`
  line
  line `(d) knowing or having reason to believe in the existence of any such mutiny, or of any intention`
  line `to mutiny or of any such conspiracy, does not, without delay, give information thereof to his`
  line `Commandant or other superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(e) endeavours to seduce any person in the Force or in the army, naval or air forces of India or`
  line `any forces cooperating therewith from his duty or allegiance to the Union,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer death or such less punishment as is in`
  line `this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (6897)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Desertion and aiding desertion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6897&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who deserts or attempts to`
  line `desert the service shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court,—`
  line
  line `(a) if he commits the offence when on active duty or when under orders for active duty, be liable`
  line `to suffer death or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he commits the offence under any other circumstances, be liable to suffer imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who knowingly harbours any such deserter shall, on conviction by`
  line `an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or`
  line `such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person subject to this Act who, being cognizant of any desertion or attempt at desertion of a`
  line `person subject to this Act, does not forthwith give notice to his own or some other superior officer, or take`
  line `any steps in his power to cause such person to be apprehended, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such less punishment`
  line `as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (6898)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6898&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) absents himself without leave; or`
  line
  line `(b) without sufficient cause, overstays leave granted to him; or`
  line
  line `(c) being on leave of absence and having received information from the appropriate authority that`
  line `any battalion or part thereof or any other unit of the Force, to which he belongs, has been ordered on`
  line `active duty, fails, without sufficient cause, to rejoin without delay; or`
  line
  line `(d) without sufficient cause, fails to appear at the time fixed at the parade or place appointed for`
  line `exercise or duty; or`
  line
  line `(e) when on parade, or on the line of march, without sufficient cause or without leave from his`
  line `superior officer, quits the parade or line of march ; or`
  line
  line `(f) when in camp or elsewhere, is found beyond any limits fixed, or in any place prohibited, by`
  line `any general, local or other order, without a pass or written leave from his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(g) without leave from his superior officer or without due cause, absents himself from any school`
  line `when duly ordered to attend there, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (6899)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Striking or threatening superior officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6899&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) uses criminal force to or assaults his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses threatening language to such officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) uses insubordinate language to such officer,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court,—`
  line
  line `(A) if such officer is at the time in the execution of his office or, if the offence is committed on`
  line `active duty, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or such`
  line `less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(B) in other cases, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years or`
  line `such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an offence specified in clause (c), the imprisonment shall not exceed five`
  line years
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (6900)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Disobedience to superior officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6900&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys, in such`
  line `manner as to show a wilful defiance of authority, any lawful command given personally by his superior`
  line `officer in the execution of his office whether the same is given orally, or in writing or by signal or`
  line `otherwise, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys any lawful command given by his superior officer`
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court,—`
  line
  line `(a) if he commits such offence when on active duty, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he commits such offence when not on active duty, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (6901)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Insubordination and obstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6901&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) being concerned in any quarrel,`
  line `affray or disorder, refuses to obey any officer, though of`
  line `inferior rank, who orders him into arrest, or uses criminal force to or assaults any such officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses criminal force to, or assaults any person, whether subject to this Act or not, in whose`
  line `custody he is lawfully placed, and whether he is or is not his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) resists an escort whose duty it is to apprehend him or to have him in charge; or`
  line
  line `(d) breaks out of barracks, camp or quarters; or`
  line
  line `(e) neglects to obey any general, local or other order ;or`
  line
  line `(f) impedes the Force Police referred to in section 85 or any person lawfully acting on its behalf,`
  line `or when called upon, refuses to assist in the execution of his duty a Force Police or any person`
  line `lawfully acting on his behalf,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend, in the case of the offences specified in clauses (d) and (e), to two years, and in the case of the`
  line `offences specified in the other clauses, to ten years, or in either case such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (6902)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Fraudulent enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6902&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who knowingly attempts to get enrolled`
  line `or enrolls any other person who does not fulfil the conditions enabling him to be enrolled, shall, on`
  line `conviction by the Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (6903)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `False answers on enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6903&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person having become subject to this Act who is discovered`
  line `to have made at the time of enrolment a wilfully false answer to any question set-forth in the prescribed`
  line `form of enrolment which has been put to him by the enrolling officer before whom he appears for the`
  line `purpose of being enrolled, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (6904)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Unbecoming conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6904&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any officer, subordinate officer or an under-officer who behaves in a`
  line `manner unbecoming his position and the character expected of him shall, on conviction by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court, be liable to be dismissed or to suffer such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (6905)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Certain forms of disgraceful conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6905&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) is guilty of any disgraceful conduct of a cruel, indecent or unnatural kind; or`
  line
  line `(b) malingers, or feigns or produces disease or infirmity in himself or intentionally delays his cure`
  line `or aggravates his disease or infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to render himself or any other person unfit for service, voluntarily causes hurt to`
  line `himself or that person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (6906)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Ill-treating a subordinate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6906&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any officer, subordinate officer or an under-officer who uses`
  line `criminal force to or otherwise ill-treats any person subject to this Act, being his subordinate in rank or position, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (6907)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title Intoxication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6907&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who is found in a state of intoxication whether on`
  line `duty or not, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (6908)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Permitting escape of person in custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6908&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) when in command of guard, picket, patrol or post, releases without proper authority, whether`
  line `wilfully or without reasonable excuse, any person committed to his charge, or refuses to receive any`
  line `prisoner or person so committed; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully or without reasonable excuse allows to escape any person who is committed to his`
  line `charge, or whom it is his duty to keep or guard,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable, if he has acted wilfully, to suffer imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he`
  line `has not acted wilfully, to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (6909)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Irregularity in connection with arrest or confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6909&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits any of the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) unnecessarily detains a person in arrest or confinement without bringing him to trial, or fails`
  line `to bring his case before the proper authority for investigation; or`
  line
  line `(b) having committed a person to Force custody fails without reasonable cause to deliver at the`
  line `time of such committal, or as soon as practicable, and in any case within forty-eight hours thereafter,`
  line `to the officer or other person into whose custody the person arrested is committed, an account in`
  line `writing signed by himself of the offence with which the person so committed is charged,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (6910)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Escape from custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6910&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who, being in lawful custody, escapes or`
  line `attempts to escape, shall on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (6911)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Offences in respect of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6911&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) commits theft of any property belonging to the Government, or to any Force mess, band, or`
  line `institution, or to any person subject to this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) dishonestly misappropriates or converts to his own use any such property; or`
  line
  line `(c) commits criminal breach of trust in respect of any such property; or`
  line
  line `(d) dishonestly receives or retains any such property in respect of which any of the offences under`
  line `clauses (a), (b) and (c) has been committed, knowing or having reason to believe the commission of`
  line `such offence; or`
  line
  line `(e) wilfully destroys or injures any property of the Government entrusted to him; or`
  line
  line `(f) does any other thing with intent to defraud, or to cause wrongful gain to one person or`
  line `wrongful loss to another person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (6912)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Extortion and corruption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6912&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) commits extortion; or`
  line
  line `(b) without proper authority extracts from any person money, provisions or service,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (6913)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Making away with equipment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6913&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) makes away with, or is concerned in making away with any arms, ammunition, equipment,`
  line `instruments, tools, clothing or any other thing being the property of the Government issued to him for`
  line `his use or entrusted to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) loses by neglect anything mentioned in clause (a); or`
  line
  line `(c) sells, pawns, destroys or defaces any medal or decoration granted to him,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend, in the case of the offences specified in clause (a), to ten years, and in the case of the offences`
  line `specified in the other clauses, to five years, or in either case such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (6914)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Injury to property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6914&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences,`
  line `that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) destroys or injures any property mentioned in clause (a) of section 41 or any property`
  line `belonging to any Force mess, band or institution, or to any person subject to this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) commits any act which causes damage to, or destruction of, any property of the Government`
  line `by fire; or`
  line
  line `(c) kills, injures, makes away with, ill-treats or loses any animal entrusted to him,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable, if he has acted wilfully, to suffer imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he`
  line `has acted without reasonable excuse, to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or`
  line `such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (6915)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `False accusations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6915&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences,`
  line `that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) makes a false accusation against any person subject to this Act, knowing or having reason to`
  line `believe such accusation to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) in making complaint against any person subject to this Act, makes any statement affecting the`
  line `character of such person, knowing or having reason to believe such statement to be false, or`
  line `knowingly and wilfully suppresses any material facts,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (6916)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Falsifying official document and false declarations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6916&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits any of the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) in any report, return, list, certificate, book or other document made or signed by him, or of the`
  line `contents of which it is his duty to ascertain the accuracy, knowingly makes, or is privy to the making`
  line `of, any false or fraudulent statement; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any document of the description mentioned in clause (a), knowingly makes, or is privy to`
  line `the making of, any omission, with intent to defraud; or`
  line
  line `(c) knowingly and with intent to injure any person or knowingly and with intent to defraud,`
  line `suppresses, defaces, alters or makes away with any document which it is his duty to preserve or`
  line `produce; or`
  line
  line `(d) where it is his official duty to make a declaration respecting any matter, knowingly makes a`
  line `false declaration; or`
  line
  line `(e) obtains for himself, or for any other person, any pension, allowance or other advantage or`
  line `privilege by a statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not`
  line `believe to be true, or by making or using false entry in any book or record, or by making any`
  line `document containing a false statement, or by omitting to make a true entry or document containing a`
  line `true statement,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (6917)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Signing in blank and failure to report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6917&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) when signing any document relating to pay, arms, ammunition, equipment, clothing, supplies`
  line `or stores, or any property of the Government fraudulently leaves in blank any material part for which`
  line `his signature is a voucher; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses or by culpable neglect omits to make or send a report or return which it is his duty to`
  line `make or send,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (6918)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Offences relating to Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6918&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) being duly summoned or ordered to attend as a witness before an Assam Rifles Court, wilfully`
  line `or without reasonable excuse, makes default in attending; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to take an oath or make an affirmation legally required by an Assam Rifles Court to be`
  line `taken or made; or`
  line
  line `(c) refuses to produce or deliver any document in his power or control legally required by an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court to be produced or delivered by him; or`
  line
  line `(d) refuses, when a witness, to answer any question which he is by law bound to answer; or`
  line
  line `(e) is guilty of contempt of the Assam Rifles Court by using insulting or threatening language, or`
  line `by causing any interruption or disturbance in the proceedings of such Court,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (6919)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `False evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6919&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who, having been duly sworn or affirmed before`
  line `any Assam Rifles Court or other court competent under this Act to administer an oath or affirmation,`
  line `makes any statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe`
  line `to be true, shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (6920)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Unlawful detention of pay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6920&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Any officer, subordinate officer or an under-officer who, having`
  line `received the pay of a person subject to this Act, unlawfully detains or refuses to pay the same when due,`
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (6921)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Violation of good order and discipline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6921&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who is guilty of any act`
  line `or omission which, though not specified in this Act, is prejudicial to good order and discipline of the`
  line `Force shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (6922)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Miscellaneous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6922&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) being in command at any post or on the march, and receiving a complaint that anyone under`
  line `his command has beaten or otherwise mal-treated or oppressed any person, or has disturbed any fair`
  line `or market, or committed any riot or trespass, fails to have due reparation made to the injured person`
  line `or to report the case to the proper authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) by defiling any place of worship, or otherwise, intentionally insults the religion, or wounds the`
  line `religious feelings of any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) attempts to commit suicide, and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of such`
  line `offence; or`
  line
  line `(d) being below the rank of subordinate officer, when off duty, appears without proper authority,`
  line `in or about camp, or when going, to, or returning from, any town or bazaar, carrying a rifle, sword or`
  line `other offensive weapons; or`
  line
  line `(e) directly or indirectly accepts or obtains, or agrees to accept or attempts to obtain, for himself`
  line `or for any other person, any gratification as a motive or reward for procuring the enrolment of any`
  line `person or leave of absence, promotion or any other advantage or indulgence for any person in the`
  line `service; or`
  line
  line `(f) commits any offence against the property or person of any inhabitant of, or resident in, the`
  line `country in which he is serving,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by an Assam, Rifles Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (6923)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title Attempt.
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6923&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who attempts to commit any of the offences specified`
  line `in sections 21 to 50 (both inclusive) and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of the`
  line `offence shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, where no express provision is made by this Act`
  line `for the punishment of such attempt, be liable,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with death, to suffer imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with imprisonment to suffer`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one-half of the longest term provided for that offence`
  line `or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (6924)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Abetment of offences that have been committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6924&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who abets the`
  line `commission of any of the offences specified in sections 21 to 50 (both inclusive) shall, on conviction by`
  line `an Assam Rifles Court, if the Act abetted is committed in consequence of the abetment and no express`
  line `provision is made by this Act for the punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer the punishment`
  line `provided for that offence or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (6925)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Abetment of offences punishable with death and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6925&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who abets the commission of any of the offences punishable with death under sections 21, 24 and`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 25 shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, if that offence,`
  line `be not committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Act for the`
  line `punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen`
  line `years of such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (6926)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Abetment of offences punishable with imprisonment and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6926&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `subject to this Act who abets the commission of any of the offences specified in sections 21 to 50 (both`
  line `inclusive) and punishable with imprisonment shall, on conviction by an Assam Rifles Court, if that`
  line `offence, be not committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Act`
  line `for the punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one-half of the longest term provided for that offence or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (6927)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Civil offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6927&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 56, any person subject to this Act who at any`
  line `place in, or beyond, India commits any civil offence shall be deemed to be guilty of an offence against`
  line `this Act and, if charged therewith under this section, shall be liable to be tried by an Assam Rifles Court`
  line `and, on conviction, be punishable as follows, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is one which would be punishable under any law in force in India with death, he`
  line `shall be liable to suffer any punishment assigned for the offence, by the aforesaid law and such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, he shall be liable to suffer any punishment assigned for the offence by the`
  line `law in force in India, or imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or such less`
  line `punishment as in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (6928)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Civil offences not triable by an Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6928&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `A person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits an offence of murder or of culpable homicide not amounting to murder against, or of rape in`
  line `relation to, a person not subject to this Act shall not be deemed to be guilty of an offence against this Act`
  line `and shall not be tried by an Assam Rifles Court, unless he commits any of the said offences,—`
  line
  line `(a) while on active duty; or`
  line
  line `(b) at any place outside India; or`
  line
  line `(c) at any place specified by the Central Government, by notification in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (6929)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Punishment awardable by Assam Rifles Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6929&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Punishments may be inflicted in respect`
  line `of offences committed by persons subject to this Act and convicted by the Assam Riles Courts, according`
  line `to the scale following, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) death;`
  line
  line `(b) imprisonment which may be for the term of life or any other lesser term but excluding`
  line `imprisonment for a term not exceeding three months in Force custody;`
  line
  line `(c) dismissal from the service;`
  line
  line `(d) compulsory retirement from service;`
  line
  line `(e) imprisonment for a term not exceeding three months in Force custody except in case of`
  line `officers and subordinate officers;`
  line
  line `(f) reduction to the ranks or to a lower rank or grade or place in the list of their rank in the case of`
  line `an under-officer;`
  line
  line `(g) forfeiture of seniority of rank and forfeiture of all or any part of the service for the purpose of`
  line promotion;
  line
  line `(h) forfeiture of service for the purpose of increased pay, pension or any other prescribed purpose;`
  line
  line `(i) fine;`
  line
  line `(j) severe reprimand or reprimand except in the case of persons below the rank of an underofficer;`
  line
  line `(k) forfeiture of pay and allowances for a period not exceeding three months for an offence`
  line `committed on active duty;`
  line
  line `(l) forfeiture in the case of person sentenced to dismissal from the service of all arrears of pay and`
  line `allowances and other public money due to him at the time of such dismissal;`
  line
  line `(m) stoppage of pay and allowances until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence`
  line `for which he is convicted is made good`
  line
  line `(2) Each of the punishments specified in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be inferior in degree to`
  line `every punishment preceding it in the above scale.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (6930)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Alternative punishments awardable by Assam Rifles Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6930&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, an Assam Rifles Court may, on convicting a person subject to this Act of any of the offences`
  line `specified in sections 21 to 54 (both inclusive) award either the particular punishment with which the`
  line `offence is stated in the said sections to be punishable or, in lieu thereof, any of the punishments lower in`
  line `the scale set out in section 57 regard being had to the nature and degree of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (6931)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Combination of punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6931&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `A sentence of an Assam Rifles Court may award in addition to,`
  line `or without any one other punishment, the punishment specified in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `57, and any one more of the punishments specified in clauses (f) to (m) (both inclusive) of that`
  line sub-section.
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (6932)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Retention in the Force of a person convicted on active duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6932&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `When on active duty, any`
  line `enrolled person has been sentenced by an Assam Rifles Court to dismissal or to imprisonment whether`
  line `combined with dismissal or not, the prescribed officer may direct that such person may be retained to`
  line `serve in the ranks, and such service shall be reckoned as part of his term of imprisonment, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (6933)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Punishments otherwise than by Assam Rifles Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6933&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Punishments may also be inflicted in`
  line `respect of offences committed by persons subject to this Act without the intervention of an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court in the manner stated in sections 62, 64, 65 and 66.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (6934)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Minor punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6934&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 63, a Commandant or such other`
  line `officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by the Director-General may, in the`
  line `prescribed manner, proceed against a person subject to this Act, otherwise than as an officer or a`
  line `subordinate officer or a Warrant Officer who is charged with an offence under this Act and award such`
  line `person to the extent prescribed, one or more of the following punishments, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) imprisonment in Force custody up to twenty-eight days;`
  line
  line `(b) detention up to twenty-eight days;`
  line
  line `(c) confinement to the lines up to twenty-eight days;`
  line
  line `(d) extra guards or duties;`
  line
  line `(e) deprivation of any special position or special emoluments or any acting rank or reduction to a`
  line `lower grade of pay;`
  line
  line `(f) forfeiture of good service and good conduct pay;`
  line
  line `(g) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(h) fine up to fourteen day's pay in any one month;`
  line
  line `(i) deduction from his pay and allowances of any sum required to make good such compensation`
  line `for any expense, loss, damage or destruction caused by him to the Central Government, or any`
  line `building or property as may be awarded by his Commandant.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (6935)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Limit of punishments under section 62.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6935&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of an award of two or more of the`
  line `punishments specified in clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d) of section 62, the punishments specified in clause (c)`
  line `or clause (d) shall take effect only at the end of the punishment specified in clause (a) or clause (b).`
  line
  line `(2) When two or more of the punishments specified in the said clauses (a), (b) and (c) are awarded to`
  line `a person conjointly, or when already undergoing one or more of the said punishments, the whole extent of`
  line `the punishments shall not exceed in the aggregate forty-two days.`
  line
  line `(3) The punishments specified in the said clauses (a), (b) and (c) shall not be awarded to any person`
  line `who is of the rank of an under-officer or was at the time of committing the offence for which he is`
  line `punished of such rank.`
  line
  line `(4) The punishments specified in clause (g) of section 62 shall not be awarded to any person below`
  line `the rank of an under-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (6936)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Punishment of officers below the rank of Deputy Commandant, subordinate officers and Warrant Officer by Deputy Inspectors-General and others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6936&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) An officer not below the rank of the`
  line `Deputy Inspector-General or such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government,`
  line `specified by the Director-General may, in the prescribed manner, proceed against an officer below the`
  line `rank of a Deputy Commandant and of any rank of subordinate officer and of the rank of Warrant Officer`
  line `who is charged with an offence under this Act and award one or more of the following punishments, that`
  line `is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) forfeiture of seniority, or in the case of any of them whose promotion depends upon the length`
  line `of service, forfeiture of service for the purpose of promotion for a period not exceeding twelve`
  line `months, but subject to the right of the accused previous to the award to elect to be tried by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court;`
  line
  line `(b) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(c) stoppage of pay and allowances until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence of`
  line `which he is convicted is made good.`
  line
  line `(2) In every case in which punishment has been awarded under sub-section (1), certified true copies`
  line `of the proceedings shall be forwarded, in the prescribed manner, by the officer awarding the punishment`
  line `to the prescribed superior authority who may, if the punishment awarded, appears to him to be illegal,`
  line `unjust or excessive, cancel, vary or remit the punishment and make such other direction as may be`
  line `appropriate in the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (6937)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Punishment of officers below the rank of a Commandant, subordinate officers and Warrant Officer by the Inspectors-General and others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6937&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) An officer not below the rank of the InspectorGeneral`
  line `or such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by the DirectorGeneral`
  line `may, in the prescribed manner, proceed against an officer below the rank of a Commandant and`
  line `any subordinate officer and a Warrant Officer who is charged with an offence under this Act and award`
  line `one or more of the following punishment, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) forfeiture of seniority, or in the case of any of them whose promotion depends upon the length`
  line `of service, forfeiture of service for the purpose of promotion for a period not exceeding twelve`
  line `months, but subject to the right of the accused previous to the award to elect to be tried by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court;`
  line
  line `(b) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(c) stoppage of pay and allowances until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence of`
  line `which he is convicted is made good.`
  line
  line `(2) In every case in which punishment has been awarded under sub-section (1), certified true copies`
  line `of the proceedings shall be forwarded, in the prescribed manner, by the officer awarding the punishment`
  line `to the prescribed superior authority who may, if the punishment awarded appears to him to be illegal,`
  line `unjust or excessive, cancel, vary or remit the punishment and make such other direction as may be`
  line `appropriate in the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (6938)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Punishment or subordinate officers and Warrant Officer by Commandant, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6938&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line A
  line `Commandant or such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by the`
  line `Director-General may, in the prescribed manner, proceed against any subordinate officer or a Warrant`
  line `Officer who is charged with an offence under this Act and award one or more of the following`
  line `punishments, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(b) stoppage of pay and allowances until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence of`
  line `which he is convicted is made good:`
  line
  line `Provided that the punishment mentioned under clause (a) shall only be awarded by an officer not`
  line `below the rank of Commandant authorised by the Director-General to award such punishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (6939)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Collective fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6939&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any weapon or part of a weapon, or ammunition, forming part of`
  line `the equipment of a unit of the Force, is lost or stolen, an officer not below rank of the Commandant of a`
  line `battalion may, after making such inquiry as he thinks fit and subject to the rules and regulations, impose a`
  line `collective fine upon the subordinate officer, under-officer and men of such unit, or upon so many of them`
  line `as, in his judgment, should be held responsible for such loss or theft.`
  line
  line `(2) Such fine shall be assessed as a percentage on the pay of the individuals on whom it falls.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (6940)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Deductions from pay and allowances of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6940&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The following penal deductions may be`
  line `made from the pay and allowances of an officer, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) all pay and allowances due to an officer for every day he absent himself without leave, unless`
  line `a satisfactory explanation has been given to his commanding officer and has been approved by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all pay and allowances for every day while he is in custody or under suspension from duty on`
  line `a charge for an offence for which he is afterwards convicted by a criminal court or an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court or by an officer exercising authority under section 64 or section 65;`
  line
  line `(c) any sum required to make good the pay of any person subject to this Act which he has`
  line `unlawfully retained or unlawfully refused to pay;`
  line
  line `(d) any sum required to make good such compensation for any expenses, loss, damage or`
  line `destruction occasioned by the commission of an offence as may be determined by an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court by whom he is convicted of such offence or by an officer exercising authority under section 64`
  line `or section 65;`
  line
  line `(e) all pay and allowances ordered by an Assam Rifles Court to be forfeited or stopped;`
  line
  line `(f) any sum required to pay a fine awarded by a criminal court or an Assam Rifles Court;`
  line
  line `(g) any sum required to make good any loss, damage or destruction of public or regimental`
  line `property which, after due investigation, appears to the Central Government to have been occasioned`
  line `by the wrongful act or negligence on the part of the officer;`
  line
  line `(h) all pay and allowances forfeited by order of the Central Government if the officer is found by`
  line `a Court of inquiry constituted by the Director-General in this behalf, to have deserted to the enemy, or`
  line `while in enemy hands, to have served with, or under the orders of, the enemy, or in any manner to`
  line `have aided the enemy, or to have allowed himself to be taken prisoner by the enemy through want of`
  line `due precaution or through disobedience of orders or wilful neglect of duty, or having been taken`
  line `prisoner by the enemy, to have failed to rejoin his service when it was possible to do so;`
  line
  line `(i) any sum required by order of the Central Government to be paid for the maintenance of his`
  line `wife or his legitimate or illegitimate child or towards the cost of any relief given by the said`
  line `Government to the said wife or child.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (6941)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Deductions from pay and allowances of persons other than officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6941&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 72, the following penal deductions may be made from the pay and allowances of a`
  line `person subject to this Act other than an officer, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) all pay and allowances for every day of absence either on desertion or without leave, or as a`
  line `prisoner of war unless a satisfactory explanation has been given and accepted by his Commandant,`
  line `and for every day of imprisonment awarded by a criminal court, an Assam Rifles Court or an officer`
  line `exercising authority under section 62;`
  line
  line `(b) all pay and allowances for every day while he is in custody on charge for an offence of which`
  line `he is afterwards convicted by a criminal court or an Assam Rifles Court or on a charge of absence`
  line `without leave for which he is afterwards awarded imprisonment by an officer exercising authority`
  line `under section 62;`
  line
  line `(c) all pay and allowances for every day on which he is in hospital on account of sickness`
  line `certified by the medical officer attending on him to have been caused by an offence under this Act`
  line `committed by him;`
  line
  line `(d) for every day on which he is in hospital on account of sickness certified by the medical officer`
  line `attending on him to have been caused by his own misconduct or imprudence, such sum as may be`
  line `specified by the order of the Central Government or such officer as may be specified by that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) all pay and allowances ordered by an Assam Rifles Court or by an officer exercising authority`
  line `under any of the sections 62, 64, 65 and 66 to be forfeited or stopped;`
  line
  line `(f) all pay and allowances for every day between his being recovered from the enemy and his`
  line `dismissal from the service in consequence of his conduct when being taken prisoner by, or while in`
  line `the hands of the enemy;`
  line
  line `(g) any sum required to make good such compensation for any expenses, loss, damage or`
  line `destruction caused by him to the Central Government or to any building or property as may be`
  line `awarded by his Commandant;`
  line
  line `(h) any sum required to pay a fine awarded by a criminal court, an Assam Rifles Court or an`
  line `officer exercising authority under any of the sections 62 and 67;`
  line
  line `(i) any sum required by order of the Central Government or any prescribed officer to be paid for`
  line `the maintenance of his wife or his legitimate or illegitimate child or towards the cost of any relief`
  line `given by the said Government to the said wife or child.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (6942)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Computation of time of absence or custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6942&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of clauses (a) and (b) of section`
  line 69,
  line
  line `(a) no person shall be treated as absent or in custody for a day unless the absence or custody has`
  line `lasted, whether wholly in one day, or partly in one day and partly in another, for six consecutive hours`
  line `or upwards;`
  line
  line `(b) any absence or custody for less than a day may be reckoned as absence or custody for a day if`
  line `such absence or custody prevented the absentee from fulfilling any duty which was thereby thrown`
  line `upon some other person;`
  line
  line `(c) absence or custody for twelve consecutive hours or upward may be reckoned as absence or`
  line `custody for the whole of each day during any portion of which the person was absent or in custody;`
  line
  line `(d) a period of absence or imprisonment, which commences before, and ends after, midnight may`
  line `be reckoned as a day.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (6943)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Pay and allowances during trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6943&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `In case of any person subject to this Act who is in custody or`
  line `under suspension from duty on a charge for an offence, the prescribed officer may direct that the whole or`
  line `any part of the pay and allowances of such person shall be withheld, pending the result of his trial on the`
  line `charge against him, in order to give effect to the provisions of clause (b) of section 68 and section 69.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (6944)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Limit of certain deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6944&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The total deductions from the pay and allowances of a person`
  line `made under clauses (e), (g) to (i) of section 69 shall not, except where he is sentenced to dismissal or`
  line `removal, exceed in any one month one-half of his pay and allowances of that month.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (6945)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Deduction from public money due to a person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6945&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Any sum authorised by this Act to be`
  line `deducted from the pay and allowances of any person may, without prejudice to any other mode of`
  line `recovering the same, be deducted from any public money due to him other than a pension.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (6946)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Pay and allowances of prisoner of war during inquiry into his conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6946&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Where the conduct`
  line `of any person subject to this Act when being taken prisoner by, or while in the hands of the enemy, is to`
  line `be inquired into this Act or any other law, the Director-General or any officer authorised by him may`
  line `order that the whole or any part of the pay and allowances of such person shall be withheld pending the`
  line `result of such inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (6947)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Remission of deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6947&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Any deduction from pay and allowances authorised by this Act may`
  line `be remitted in such manner and to such extent and by such authority, as may, from time to time be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (6948)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Provision for dependants of prisoner of war from remitted deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6948&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `In the case of all`
  line `persons subject to this Act, being prisoners of war, whose pay and allowances have been forfeited under`
  line `clause (a) of section 69, but in respect of whom a remission has been made under section 75, it shall be`
  line `lawful for proper provision to be made by the prescribed authorities out of such pay and allowances for`
  line `any dependants of such persons, and any such remission shall in that case be deemed to apply only to the`
  line `balance thereafter remaining of such pay and allowances.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (6949)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Provision for dependants of prisoner of war from his pay and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6949&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful`
  line `for proper provision to be made by the prescribed authorities for any dependants of any person subject to`
  line `this Act who is prisoner of war or is missing, out of his pay and allowances.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (6950)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Period during which a person is deemed to be a prisoner of war.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6950&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `sections 76 and 77, a person shall be deemed to continue to be prisoner of war until the conclusion of any`
  line `inquiry into his conduct such as is referred to in section 74 and if he is dismissed or removed from the`
  line `service in consequence of such conduct, until the date of such dismissal or removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (6951)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Custody of offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6951&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who is charged with an offence may`
  line `be taken into Force custody, under the order of any superior officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an officer may order into Force custody`
  line `any other officer, though such other officer may be of a higher rank, engaged in a quarrel, affray or`
  line disorder.
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (6952)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Duty of Commandant in regard to detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6952&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every Commandant to`
  line `take care that a person under his command when charged with an offence is not detained in custody for`
  line `more than forty-eight hours after the committal of such person into custody is reported to him without the`
  line `charge being investigated, unless investigation within that period seems to him to be impracticable having`
  line `regard to the public service.`
  line
  line `(2) The case of every person, being detained in custody beyond a period of forty-eight hours, and`
  line `reason thereof, shall be reported by the Commandant to the Deputy Inspector-General under whom he is`
  line `serving or such other officer to whom an application may be made to convene as Assam Rifles Court for`
  line `the trial of the person charged.`
  line
  line `(3) In reckoning the period of forty-eight hours specified in sub-section (1), sundays and other public`
  line `holidays shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may make rules providing for the`
  line `manner in which and the period for which any person subject to this Act may be taken into and detained`
  line `in Force custody, pending the trial by any competent authority for any offence committed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (6953)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Interval between committal and trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6953&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `In every case where any such person as is mentioned in`
  line `section 79 and as not on active duty, remains in such custody for a longer period than eight days, without`
  line `his trial by an Assam Rifles Court being ordered to be convened, a special report giving reasons for the`
  line `delay shall be made by his Commandant in the manner prescribed, and a similar report shall be forwarded`
  line `at intervals of every eight days until an Assam Rifles Court is convened or such person is released from`
  line custody.
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (6954)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Arrest by civil authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6954&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person subject to this Act who is accused of an`
  line `offence under this Act, is within the jurisdiction of any magistrate or police officer, such magistrate or`
  line `police officer shall aid in the apprehension and delivery to Force custody of such person upon receipt of a`
  line `written application to that effect signed by his Commandant or an officer authorised by the Commandant`
  line `in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (6955)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Capture of deserters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6955&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any person subject to this Act deserts, the Commandant of`
  line `the unit to which he belongs, shall give information of the desertion to such civil authorities as, in his`
  line `opinion, may be able to afford assistance towards the capture of the deserter; and such authorities shall`
  line `thereupon take steps for the apprehension of the said deserter in like manner as if he were a person for`
  line `whose apprehension a warrant had been issued by a magistrate and shall deliver the deserter, when`
  line `apprehended, into Force custody.`
  line
  line `(2) Any police officer may arrest without warrant any person reasonably believed to be subject to this`
  line `Act, and to be a deserter or to be travelling without authority, and shall bring him without delay before the`
  line `nearest magistrate, to be dealt with according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (6956)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Inquiry into absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6956&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to this Act has been absent`
  line `from his duty without due authority for a period of thirty days, a court of inquiry shall, as soon as`
  line `practicable, be assembled and such court shall, on oath or affirmation administered in the prescribed`
  line `manner, inquire respecting the absence of the person, and the deficiency, if any, in the property of the`
  line `Government entrusted to his care, or in any arms, ammunition, equipment, instruments, clothing or`
  line `necessaries; and if satisfied of the fact of such absence without due authority or other sufficient cause, the`
  line `court shall declare such absence and the period thereof and the said deficiency, if any, and the`
  line `Commandant of the unit to which the person belongs shall make a record thereof in the prescribed`
  line manner.
  line
  line `(2) If the person declared absent does not afterwards surrender or is not apprehended, he shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, be deemed to be deserter.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (6957)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Force Police Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6957&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General or any prescribed officer may appoint persons`
  line `(in this Act referred to as Force Police) for discharging the functions specified in sub-sections (2) and (3).`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of a person appointed under sub-section (1), are to take charge of persons confined for`
  line `any offence, to preserve good order and discipline and to prevent breaches of the same by persons serving`
  line `in, or attached to, the Force.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 79, a person appointed under sub-section (1) may,`
  line `at any time, arrest and detain for trial, any person subject to this Act who commits, or is charged with, an`
  line `offence, and may also carry into effect any punishment to be inflicted in pursuance of a sentence awarded`
  line `by an Assam Rifles Court or by an officer exercising authority under section 62 but shall not inflict any`
  line `punishment on his own authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no officer shall be arrested or detained otherwise than on the order of another officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (6958)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Kinds of Assam Rifles Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6958&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act there shall be three kinds of Assam`
  line `Rifles Courts, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) General Assam Rifles Courts;`
  line
  line `(b) Petty Assam Rifles Courts; and`
  line
  line `(c) Summary Assam Rifles Courts.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (6959)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to convene a General Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6959&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `A General Assam Rifles Court may be`
  line `convened by the Central Government or the Director-General or by any officer empowered in this behalf`
  line `by warrant of the Director-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (6960)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power to convene a Petty Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6960&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `A Petty Assam Rifles Court may be convened`
  line `by an officer having power to convene a General Assam Rifles Court or by an officer empowered in this`
  line `behalf by warrant of any such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (6961)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Contents of warrants issued under sections 87 and 88.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6961&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `A warrant issued under section 87 or`
  line `section 88 may contain such restrictions, reservations or conditions as the officer issuing it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (6962)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Composition of General Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6962&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `A General Assam Rifles Court shall consist of`
  line `not less than five officers, each of whom has held the post of Assistant Commandant for not less thanthree whole years and of whom not less than four are of a rank not below that of confirmed Assistant`
  line Commandant.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section and section 91, "Assistant Commandant" includes any`
  line `post of a higher rank and any post declared by the Central Government, by notification, to be an`
  line `equivalent post as also any post higher in rank than the post so declared.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (6963)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Composition of a Petty Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6963&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `A Petty Assam Rifles Court shall consist of not`
  line `less than three officers each of whom has held the post of Assistant Commandant for not less than two`
  line `whole years.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (6964)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Summary Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6964&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Summary Assam Rifles Court may be held by the`
  line `Commandant of any unit of the Force and he alone shall constitute the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The proceeding shall be attended throughout by two other persons who shall be officers or`
  line `subordinate officers or one of either, and who shall not as such, be sworn or affirmed.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (6965)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Dissolution of an Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6965&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an Assam Rifles Court after the commencement`
  line `of a trial is reduced below the minimum number of officers required by this Act, it shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on account of the illness of the Law Officer or of the accused before the finding, it is`
  line `impossible to continue the trial, an Assam Rifles Court shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer who convened an Assam Rifles Court may dissolve the same if it appears to him that`
  line `the exigencies of the service or necessities of discipline render it imposible or inexpedient to continue the`
  line `said Assam Rifles Court.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an Assam Rifles Court is dissolved under this section, the accused may be tried again.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (6966)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power of General Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6966&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `A General Assam Rifles Court shall have the power to`
  line `try any person subject to this Act for any offence punishable thereunder and to pass any sentence`
  line `authorised thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (6967)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Power of a Petty Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6967&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `A Petty Assam Rifles Court shall have power to try any`
  line `person subject to this Act other than an officer or a subordinate officer for any offence made punishable`
  line `thereunder and to pass any sentence authorised by this Act other than a sentence of death or imprisonment`
  line `for a term exceeding two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (6968)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power of a Summary Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6968&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), a`
  line `Summary Assam Rifles Court may try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) When there is no grave reason for immediate action and reference can, without detriment to`
  line `discipline, be made to the officer empowered to convene a Petty Assam Rifles Court for the trial of the`
  line `alleged offender, an officer holding a Summary Assam Rifles Court shall not try without such reference`
  line `any offence punishable under any of the sections 21, 24 and 55, or any offence against the officer holding`
  line `the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) A Summary Assam Rifles Court may try any person subject to this Act and under the command of`
  line `the officer holding the Court, except an officer or a subordinate officer.`
  line
  line `(4) A Summary Assam Rifles Court may pass any sentence which may be passed under this Act`
  line `except the sentence of death or if imprisonment for a term exceeding the limit specified in sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(5) The limit referred to in sub-section (4) shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) one year, if the officer holding the Assam Rifles Court has held either the post of`
  line `Commandant or a post declared by the Central Government, by notification, to be equivalent thereto`
  line `for a period of not less than three years or holds a post of higher rank than either of the said posts; and`
  line
  line `(b) three months, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (6969)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Prohibition of second trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6969&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to this Act has been acquitted or`
  line `convicted of an offence by an Assam Rifles Court or by a criminal court or has been dealt with under section 62 or section 64 or section 65 or section 66, he shall not be liable to be tried again for the same`
  line `offence by an Assam Rifles Court or dealt with under the said sections.`
  line
  line `(2) When any person, subject to this Act has been acquitted or convicted of an offence by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court or has been dealt with under section 62 or section 64 or section 65 or section 66, he shall not`
  line `be liable to be tried again by a criminal court for the same offence or on the same facts.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (6970)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Period of limitation for trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6970&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided by sub-section (2), no trial by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court of any person subject to this Act for any offence shall be commenced after the expiration of a`
  line `period of three years and such period shall commence—`
  line
  line `(a) on the date of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the commission of the offence was not known to the person aggrieved by the offence or`
  line `to the authority competent to initiate action, from the first day on which such offence comes to the`
  line `knowledge of such person or authority, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(c) where it is not known by whom the offence was committed, from the first day on which the`
  line `identity of the offender is known to the person aggrieved by the offence or to the authority competent`
  line `to initiate action, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing any period under this section, the period during which the proceedings of`
  line `investigation has been stayed by any court in such offence by injunction or order, the period of the`
  line `continuance of the injunction or order, the day on which it was issued or made; and the day on which it`
  line `was withdrawn, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to a trial for an offence of desertion or for any of`
  line `the offences mentioned in section 24 or an offence under section 30.`
  line
  line `(3) In computation of the period of three years under sub-section (1), any time spent by such person in`
  line `evading arrest after the commission of the offence, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (6971)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Trial, etc., of offender who ceases to be subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6971&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this`
  line `Act had been committed by any person while subject to this Act and he had ceased to be so subject, he`
  line `may be taken into and kept in Force custody and tried and punished for such offence as if he continued to`
  line `be so subject.`
  line
  line `(2) No such person shall be tried for an offence, unless his trial commences within a period of three`
  line `years after he had ceased to be subject to this Act; and in computing such period, the time during which`
  line `such person has avoided arrest by absconding or concealing himself or where the institution of the`
  line `proceeding in respect of the offence has been stayed by an injunction or order, the period of the`
  line `continuance of the injunction or order, the day on which it was issued or made, and the day on which it`
  line `was withdrawn, shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to the trial of any such person for an`
  line `offence of desertion or for any of the offences mentioned in section 24 or shall affect the jurisdiction of a`
  line `criminal court to try an offence triable by such court as well as by an Assam Rifles Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (6972)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Application of this Act during term of sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6972&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person subject to this Act is`
  line `sentenced by an Assam Rifles Court to imprisonment, this Act shall apply to him during the term of his`
  line `sentence, though he is dismissed from the Force or has otherwise ceased to be subject to this Act, and he`
  line `may be kept, removed, imprisoned and punished as if he continued to be subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) When a person subject to this Act is sentenced by an Assam Rifles Court to death, this Act shall`
  line `apply to him till the sentence is carried out.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (6973)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6973&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any offence against it may be tried`
  line `and punished for such offence in any place whatever.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (6974)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Choice between criminal court and Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6974&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `When a criminal court and an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court each have jurisdiction in respect of an offence, it shall be in the discretion of the`
  line `Director-General, or the Inspector General or the Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the`
  line `accused person is serving or such other officer as may be prescribed, to decide before which court proceedings shall be instituted, and, if that officer, decides that they shall be instituted before an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court, to direct that the accused person shall be detained in Force custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (6975)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power of criminal court to require delivery of offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6975&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a criminal court having`
  line `jurisdiction is of opinion that proceedings shall be instituted before itself in respect of any alleged`
  line `offence, it may, by written notice, require the officer referred to in section 102 at his option, either to`
  line `deliver over the offender to the nearest Magistrate to be proceeded against according to law, or to`
  line `postpone proceedings, pending a reference to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case the said officer shall either deliver over the offender in compliance with the`
  line `requisition, or shall forthwith refer the question as to the court before which the proceedings are to be`
  line `instituted, for the determination of the Central Government whose order upon such reference shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (6976)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Presiding officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6976&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `At every General Assam Rifles Court or Petty Assam Rifles Court, the`
  line `senior member shall be the presiding officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (6977)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Law Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6977&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Every General Assam Rifles Court shall, and every Petty Assam Rifles Court`
  line `may, be attended by a Law Officer, or if no such officer is available, an officer approved by the Chief`
  line `Law Officer or a Law Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (6978)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title Challenges.
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6978&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) At all trials by a General Assam Rifles Court or by a Petty Assam Rifles`
  line `Court, as soon as the Court is assembled, the names of the presiding officer and members shall be read`
  line `over to the accused, who shall thereupon be asked whether he objects to being tried by any officer sitting`
  line `on the court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused objects to such officer, his objection and also the reply thereto of the officer`
  line `objected to, shall be heard and recorded, and the remaining officers of the court shall, in the absence of`
  line `the challenged officer, decide on the objection.`
  line
  line `(3) If the objection is allowed by one-half or more of the votes of the officers entitled to vote, the`
  line `objection shall be allowed, and the member objected to shall retire, and his vacancy may be filled in the`
  line `prescribed manner, by another officer subject to the same right of the accused to object.`
  line
  line `(4) When no challenge is made, or when a challenge has been made and disallowed, or the place of`
  line `every officer successfully challenged has been filled by another officer to whom no objection is made or`
  line `allowed, the court shall proceed with the trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (6979)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Oath of member, Law Officer and witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6979&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) An oath or affirmation in the prescribed`
  line `manner shall be administered to every member of an Assam Rifles Court and to the Law Officer or, as the`
  line `case may be, the officer approved under section 105 before the commencement of the trial.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person giving evidence before an Assam Rifles Court shall be examined after being duly`
  line `sworn or affirmed in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall not apply where the witness is a child under twelve years`
  line `of age and the Assam Rifles Court is of opinion that though the witness understands the duty of speaking`
  line `the truth, he does not understand the nature of an oath or affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (6980)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Voting by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6980&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), every decision`
  line `of an Assam Rifles Court shall be passed by a majority of votes; and where there is an equality of votes`
  line `on either the finding or the sentence, the decision shall be in favour of the accused.`
  line
  line `(2) No sentence of death shall be passed by a General Assam Rifles Court without the concurrence of`
  line `at least two-thirds of the members of the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) In matters, other than a challenge or the finding or sentence, the presiding officer shall have a`
  line `casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (6981)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `General rule as to evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6981&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `The Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, apply to all proceedings before an Assam Rifles Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (6982)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Judicial notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6982&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `An Assam Rifles Court may take judicial notice of any matter within the`
  line `general knowledge of the members as officers of the Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (6983)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Summoning of witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6983&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) The convening officer, the presiding officer of an Assam Rifles`
  line `Court or court of inquiry or the Law Officer or, as the case may be, the officer approved under section`
  line `105 or the Commandant of the accused person may, by summons under his hand, require the attendance,`
  line `at a time and place to be mentioned in the summons, of any person either to give evidence or to produce`
  line `any document or other thing.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a witness, who is subject to this Act, the summons shall be sent to his Commandant`
  line `and such officer shall serve it upon him accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any other witness, the summons shall be sent to the Magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction he may be, or resides, and such Magistrate shall give effect to the summons as if the witness`
  line `were required in the court of such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (6984)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Documents exempted from production.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6984&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 111 shall be deemed to affect`
  line `the operation of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or to apply to any`
  line `letter, postcard, telegram or other document in the custody of the postal or telegraph authorities.`
  line
  line `(2) If any document in such custody is, in the opinion of any Chief Judicial Magistrate, Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate, Court of Session or High Court, wanted for the purpose of any Assam Rifles`
  line `Court, such Magistrate or Court may require the postal or telegraph authorities, as the case may be, to`
  line `deliver such document to such person as such Magistrate, or Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such documents is, in the opinion of any other Magistrate of any Commissioner of Police or`
  line `District Superintendent of Police, wanted for any such purpose, he may require the postal or telegraph`
  line `authorities, as the case may be, to cause such search to be made for, and to detain such document pending`
  line `the orders of any such Chief Judicial Magistrate, Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or Court of Session or`
  line `High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (6985)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Commission for examination of witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6985&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court, it appears to the Court that the examination of a witness is necessary for the ends of justice,`
  line `and that the attendance of such witness cannot be procured without an amount of delay, expense or`
  line `inconvenience which, in the circumstances of the case, would be unreasonable, such court may address`
  line `the Chief Law Officer in order that a commission to take the evidence of such witness may be issued.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Law Officer may then, if he thinks necessary, issue a commission to any Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction such`
  line `witness resides to take the evidence of such witness.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Judicial Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class to whom the commission is`
  line `issued, or if he is the Chief Judicial Magistrate, he or such Judicial Magistrate of the first class as he`
  line `appoints in this behalf, shall summon the witness before him and shall take down his evidence in the same`
  line `manner, and may for this purpose exercise the same powers, as in the trials of warrant-cases under the`
  line `Code of criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(4) When the witness resides in tribal area or in any place outside India, the commission may be`
  line `issued in the manner specified in sub-heading "B.—Commissions for the examination of witnesses" of`
  line `Chapter XXIII of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (6986)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Examination of witness on commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6986&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prosecutor and the accused person in any`
  line `case in which a commission is issued under section 113 may respectively forward any interrogatories in`
  line `writing which the court may think relevant to the issue, and the Chief Judicial Magistrate or the Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class executing the commission shall examine the witness upon such`
  line interrogatories.
  line
  line `(2) The prosecutor and the accused person may appear before such Chief Judicial Magistrate or the`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class by counsel or, except in the case of an accused person in custody, in`
  line `person, and may examine, cross-examine and re-examine, as the case may be, the said witness.`
  line
  line `(3) After a commission issued under section 113 has been duly executed, it shall be returned, together`
  line `with the deposition of the witness examined thereunder to the Chief Law Officer.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of a commission, and deposition returned under sub-section (3), the Chief Law Officer`
  line `shall forward the same to the court at whose instance the commission was issued or, if such court has`
  line `been dissolved, to any other court convened for the trial of the accused person and the commission, the`
  line `return thereto and the deposition shall be open to inspection by the prosecutor or the accused, person and`
  line `may, subject to all just exceptions, be read in evidence in the case by either the prosecutor or the accused,`
  line `and shall form part of the proceedings of the court.`
  line
  line `(5) In every case in which a commission is issued under section 113, the trial may be adjourned for`
  line `specified time reasonably sufficient for the execution and return of the commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (6987)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Conviction of offences not charged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6987&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `A person charged before an Assam Rifles Court—`
  line
  line `(a) with desertion may be found guilty of attempting to desert or of being absent without leave;`
  line
  line `(b) with attempting to desert may be found guilty of being absent without leave;`
  line
  line `(c) with using criminal force may be found guilty of assault;`
  line
  line `(d) with using threatening language may be found guilty of using insubordinate language;`
  line
  line `(e) with any one of the offences specified in clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d) of section 39 may be`
  line `found guilty of any other of these offences with which he might have been charged;`
  line
  line `(f) with an offence punishable under section 55 may be found guilty of any other offence of`
  line `which he might have been found guilty, if the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), were applicable;`
  line
  line `(g) with any offence under this Act may, on failure of proof of an offence having been committed`
  line `in circumstances involving a more severe punishment, be found guilty of the same offence as having`
  line `been committed in circumstances involving a less severe punishment;`
  line
  line `(h) with any offence under this Act may be found guilty of having attempted or abetted the`
  line `commission of that offence, although the attempt or abetment is not separately charged`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (6988)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Presumption as to signatures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6988&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, any application, certificate,`
  line `warrant, reply or other document purporting to be signed by an officer in the service of the Government`
  line `shall, on production, be presumed to have been duly signed by the person by whom and in the character in`
  line `which it purports to have been signed, until the contrary is shown.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (6989)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Enrolment paper.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6989&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any enrolment paper purporting to be signed by an enrolling officer`
  line `shall, in proceedings under this Act, be evidence of the person enrolled having given the answers to`
  line `questions which he is therein represented as having given.`
  line
  line `(2) The enrolment of such person may be proved by the production of the original or a copy of this`
  line `enrolment paper purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the officer having custody of enrolment`
  line paper
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (6990)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Presumption as to certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6990&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) A letter, return or other document respecting the`
  line `service of any person in, or the dismissal, removal or discharge of any person from, any unit of the Force,`
  line `or respecting the circumstances of any person not having served in, or belonged to any unit of the Force,`
  line `if purporting to be signed by or on behalf of the Central Government or the Director-General, or by any`
  line `prescribed officer, shall be the evidence of facts stated in such letter, return or other document.`
  line
  line `(2) An Assam Rifles list or Gazette purporting to be published by authority shall be evidence of the`
  line `status and rank of the officers, subordinate officers therein mentioned, and of any appointment held by`
  line `them and of the battalion, unit or branch of the Force to which they belong.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a record is made in any battalion book in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or otherwise`
  line `in the discharge of official duties, and purporting to be signed by the Commandant or by the officer`
  line `whose duty it is to make such record, such record shall be evidence of the facts therein stated.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of any record in any battalion book purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the`
  line `officer having custody of such book shall be evidence of such record.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of absence without`
  line `leave, and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of any officer or other person subject to`
  line `this Act, or any unit of the Force, or has been apprehended by such officer or person, a certificate`
  line `purporting to be signed by such officer or by the Commandant of the unit to which such person belongs,`
  line `as the case may be, and stating the fact, date and place of such surrender or apprehension, and the manner`
  line `in which he was dressed, shall be the evidence of the matters so stated.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of absence without`
  line `leave and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of, or has been apprehended by, a police`
  line `officer not below the rank of an officer in charge of a police station, a certificate purporting to be signed`
  line `by such police officer and stating facts, the date and place of such surrender or apprehension, and the`
  line `manner in which he was dressed shall be evidence of the matters so stated.`
  line
  line `(7) Any document purporting to be the report under the hand of a Government scientific expert, upon`
  line `any matter or thing duly submitted to him for examination or analysis and report in the course of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act, may be used as evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(8) The Assam Rifles Court may, if it thinks fit, summon and examine the expert referred to in subsection`
  line `(7) as to the subject matter of his report.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any such expert is summoned by an Assam Rifles Court and he is unable to attend`
  line `personally, he may, unless the Court has expressly directed him to appear personally, depute any`
  line `responsible officer working with him to attend the Court, if such deputed officer is conversant with the`
  line `facts of the case and satisfactorily depose in the Court on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of sub-sections (7), (8) and (9) shall apply to such Government scientific experts`
  line `as specified in sub-section (4) of section 293 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (6991)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Reference by accused to Government officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6991&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any trial for desertion or absence`
  line `without leave, overstaying leave or not rejoining when warned for service, the accused person states in his`
  line `defence any sufficient or reasonable excuse for his unauthorised absence, and refers in support thereof to`
  line `any officer in the service of the Government, or if it appears that any such officer is likely to prove or`
  line `disprove the said statement in the defence, the Court shall address such officer and adjourn the`
  line `proceedings until his reply is received.`
  line
  line `(2) The written reply of any officer so referred to shall, if signed by him, be received in evidence and`
  line `have the same effect as if made on oath before the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Court is dissolved before the receipt of such reply or if the Court omits to comply with the`
  line `provisions of this section, the convening officer may, at his discretion, annul the proceedings and order a`
  line `fresh trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (6992)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Evidence of previous convictions and general character.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6992&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to`
  line `this Act has been convicted by an Assam Rifles Court of any offence, such Assam Rifles Court may`
  line `inquire into, and receive, and record evidence of any previous convictions of such person, either by an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court or by a criminal court, or any previous award of punishment under section 62 or`
  line `section 64 or section 65 or section 66, and may further inquire into and record the general character of`
  line `such person and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Evidence received under this section may be either oral, or in the shape of entries in, or certified`
  line `extracts from, books of an Assam Rifles Court, or other official records; and it shall not be necessary to`
  line `give notice before trial to the person tried that evidence as to his previous convictions or character will be`
  line received.
  line
  line `(3) At a Summary Assam Rifles Court, the officer holding the trial may, if he thinks fit, record any`
  line `previous convictions against the offender, his general character, and such other matters as may be`
  line `prescribed, as of his own knowledge, instead of requiring them to be proved under the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (6993)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Lunacy of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6993&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by an Assam Rifles Court, it appears`
  line `to the Court that the person charged is by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of making his`
  line `defence, or that he committed the act alleged but was by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of`
  line `knowing the nature of the act or knowing that it was wrong or contrary to law, the Court shall record a`
  line `finding accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) The presiding officer of the Court, or in the case of a Summary Assam Rifles Court, the officer`
  line `holding the trial, shall forthwith report the case to the confirming officer, or to the authority empowered`
  line `to deal with its findings under section 137, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The confirming officer to whom the case is reported under sub-section (2) may, if he does not`
  line `confirm the finding, take steps to have the accused person tried by the same or another Assam Rifles`
  line `Court for the offence with which he was charged.`
  line
  line `(4) The authority to whom the finding of a Summary Assam Rifles Court is reported under subsection`
  line `(2), and a confirming officer confirming the finding in any case so reported to him shall order the`
  line `accused person to be kept in custody in the prescribed manner and shall report the case for the orders of`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of a report under sub-section (4), the Central Government may order the accused`
  line `person to be detained in a lunatic asylum or other suitable place of safe custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (6994)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Subsequent fitness of lunatic accused for trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6994&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Where any accused person, having been`
  line `found by reason of unsoundness of mind to be incapable of making his defence, is in custody or under`
  line `detention under section 121, any officer prescribed in this behalf, may,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such person is in custody under sub-section (4) of section 121, on the report of a medical`
  line `officer that he is capable of making his defence, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained in a jail under sub-section (5) of section 121 on a certificate of the`
  line `Inspector-General of Prisons, and if such person is detained in a lunatic asylum under the said subsection,`
  line `on a certificate of any two or more of the visitors of such asylum and if he is detained in any`
  line `other place under that sub-section, on a certificate of the prescribed authority, that he is capable of`
  line `making his defence,`
  line
  line `take steps to have such person tried by the same or another Assam Rifles Court for the offence with which`
  line `he was originally charged or, if the offence is a civil offence, by a criminal court.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (6995)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Transmission to Central Government of orders under section 122.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6995&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `A copy of every order`
  line `made by an officer under section 122 for the trial of the accused shall forthwith be sent to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (6996)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Release of lunatic accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6996&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is in custody under sub-section (4) of section`
  line `121 or under detention under sub-section (5) of that section,`
  line
  line `(a) if such person is in custody under the said sub-section (4), on the report of a medical officer,`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained under the said sub-section (5), on a certificate from any of the`
  line `authorities mentioned in clause (b) of section 122 that in the judgment of such officer or authority`
  line `such person may be released without danger of his doing injury to himself or to any other person,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may order that such person be released or detained in custody, or transferred to a`
  line `public lunatic asylum if he has not already been to such an asylum.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (6997)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Delivery of lunatic accused to relatives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6997&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Where any relative or friend of any person who is in`
  line `custody under sub-section (4) of section 121 or under detention under sub-section (5) of that section`
  line `desires that he should be delivered to his care and custody, the Central Government, may, uponapplication by such relative or friend and, on his giving security to the satisfaction of that Government`
  line `that the person delivered shall be properly taken care of and, prevented from doing injury to himself or to`
  line `any other person, and be produced for the inspection of such officer, and at such times and places, as the`
  line `Central Government may direct, order such person to be delivered to such relative or friend.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (6998)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Order for custody and disposal of property pending trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6998&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `When any property regarding`
  line `which any offence appears to have been committed, or which appears to have been used for the`
  line `commission any offence, is produced before an Assam Rifles Court during a trial, the Court may make`
  line `such order as it thinks fit for the proper custody of such property pending the conclusion of the trial, and`
  line `if the property is subject to speedy or natural decay may, after recording such evidence as it thinks`
  line `necessary, order it to be sold otherwise disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (6999)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Order of disposal of property regarding which offences is committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=6999&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the`
  line `conclusion of a trial before any Assam Rifles Court, the Court or the officer confirming the finding or`
  line `sentence of such Assam Rifles Court, or any authority superior to such officer, or, in the case of Summary`
  line `Assam Rifles Court whose finding or sentence does not require confirmation, an officer not below the`
  line `rank of Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the trial was held, may make such order as it or`
  line `he thinks fit for the disposal by destruction, confiscation, delivery to any person claiming to be entitled to`
  line `possession thereof, or otherwise, of any property or document produced before the Court or in its custody,`
  line `or regarding which any offence appears to have been committed or which has been committed or which`
  line `has been used for the commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any order has been made under sub-section (1) in respect of property regarding which an`
  line `offence appears to have been committed, a copy of such order signed and certified by the authority`
  line `making the same may, whether the trial was held within India or not, be sent to a Magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction such property for the time being is situated, and such Magistrate shall thereupon cause the`
  line `order to be carried into effect as if it were an order passed by him under the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the term "property" includes, in the case of property regarding which an offence`
  line `appears to have been committed, not only such property as has been originally in the possession or under`
  line `the control of any person, but also any property into or for which the same may have been converted or`
  line `exchanged, and anything acquired by such conversion or exchange whether immediately or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (7000)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Powers of Assam Rifles Court in relation to proceedings under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7000&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Any trial by an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court under the provisions of the Act shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Assam Rifles Court shall`
  line `be deemed to be the Court within the meaning of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (7001)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Finding and sentence not valid unless confirmed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7001&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `No finding or sentence of a General`
  line `Assam Rifles Court or a Petty Assam Rifles Court shall be valid except so far as it may be confirmed as`
  line `provided by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (7002)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Power to confirm finding and sentence of General Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7002&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `The findings and`
  line `sentences of General Assam Rifles Courts may be confirmed by the Central Government or by any officer`
  line `empowered in this behalf by warrant of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (7003)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Power to confirm finding and sentence of Petty Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7003&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `The findings and`
  line `sentences of Petty Assam Rifles Court may be confirmed by an officer having powers to convene a`
  line `General Assam Rifles Court or by any officer empowered in this behalf by warrant of such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (7004)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Limitation of powers of confirming authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7004&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `A warrant issued under section 130 or section`
  line `131 may contain such restrictions, reservations or conditions as the authority issuing it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (7005)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Power of confirming authority to mitigate, remit or commute sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7005&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such`
  line `restrictions, reservations or conditions, as may be contained in any warrant issued under section 130 or section 131, a confirming authority may, when confirming the sentence of an Assam Rifles Court,`
  line `mitigate or remit the punishment thereby awarded, or commute that punishment for any punishment or`
  line `punishment lower in the scale laid down in section 57.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (7006)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Confirming of findings and sentences on board a ship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7006&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `When any person subject to this Act`
  line `is tried and sentenced by an Assam Rifles Court while on board a ship, the finding and sentence so far as`
  line `not confirmed and executed on board the ship, may be confirmed and executed in like manner as if such`
  line `person had been tried at the port of disembarkation.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (7007)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Revision of finding or sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7007&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any finding or sentence of an Assam Rifles Court which`
  line `requires confirmation may be once revised by order of the confirming authority and on such revision, the`
  line `Court, if so directed by the confirming authority, may take additional evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court, on revision, shall consist of the same officers as were present when the original`
  line `decision was passed unless any of those officers are unavoidably absent.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of such unavoidable absence the cause thereof shall be duly certified in the proceedings,`
  line `and the Court shall proceed with the revision:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if a General Assam Rifles Court, still consists of five officers, or, if a Petty Assam`
  line `Rifles Court, of three officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (7008)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Finding and sentence of a Summary Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7008&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `sub-section (2), the finding and sentence of a Summary Assam Rifles Court shall not require to be`
  line `confirmed, but may be carried out forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2) If the officer holding the trial is of the rank of Deputy Commandant or of a rank declared under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (5) of section 96 as equivalent thereto or of a lower rank and has held such rank`
  line `for less than five years, he shall not, except on active duty, carry into effect any sentence, until it has`
  line `received the approval of an officer not below the rank of a Deputy Inspector-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (7009)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Transmission of proceedings of Summary Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7009&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The proceedings of every`
  line `Summary Assam Rifles Court shall, without delay, be forwarded to the officer not below the rank of`
  line `Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the trial was held, or to the prescribed officer, and such`
  line `officer or the Director General or any officer empowered by him in this behalf may, for reasons based on`
  line `the merits of the case, but not on merely technical grounds, set aside the proceedings, or reduce the`
  line `sentence to any other sentence which the court might have passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (7010)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Alteration of finding or sentence in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7010&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a finding of guilty by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court, which has been confirmed or which does not require confirmation, is found for any reason`
  line `to be invalid or cannot be supported by the evidence, the authority which would have had power under`
  line `section 150 to commute the punishment awarded by the sentence, if the finding had been valid may`
  line `substitute a new finding and pass a sentence for the offence specified or involved in such finding:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such substitution shall be made unless such finding could have been validly made by`
  line `the Assam Rifles Court on the charge and unless it appears that the Assam Rifles Court must have been`
  line `satisfied of the facts establishing the said offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a sentence passed by an Assam Rifles Court which has been confirmed, or which does not`
  line `require confirmation, not being a sentence passed in pursuance of new finding substituted under subsection(1) is found for any reason to be invalid, the authority referred to sub-section (1) may pass a valid`
  line sentence.
  line
  line `(3) The punishment awarded by a sentence passed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not`
  line `be higher in the scale of punishment than, or in excess of, the punishment awarded by, the sentence for`
  line `which a new sentence is substituted under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Any finding substituted, or any sentence passed, under this section shall, for the purpose of this`
  line `Act and the rules, have effect as if it were a finding or sentence, as the case may be, of an Assam Rifles`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (7011)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Remedy against order, finding or sentence of Assam Rifles Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7011&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject`
  line `to this Act who considers himself aggrieved by any order passed by any Assam Rifles Court may present`
  line `a petition to the officer or authority empowered to confirm any finding or sentence of the Assam Rifles`
  line `Court and the confirming authority may take such steps as may be considered necessary to satisfy itself as`
  line `to the correctness, legality or propriety of the order passed or as to regularity of any proceeding to which`
  line `the order relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who considers himself aggrieved by a finding or sentence of any`
  line `Assam Rifles Court which has been confirmed may present a petition to the Central Government, the`
  line `Director-General or any prescribed officer superior in command to the one who confirmed such finding or`
  line `sentence, and the Central Government, the Director-General or the prescribed officer, as the case may be,`
  line `may pass such order thereon as it or he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (7012)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Annulment of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7012&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, the Director-General or any prescribed`
  line `officer may annul the proceeding of any Assam Rifles Court on the ground that they are illegal or unjust.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (7013)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Form of sentence of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7013&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `In awarding a sentence of death, an Assam Rifles Court shall in`
  line `its discretion direct that the offender shall suffer death by being hanged by the neck until he be dead, or`
  line `shall suffer death by being shot to death.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (7014)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Commencement of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7014&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is sentenced by an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court under this Act to imprisonment, the term of his sentence shall, whether it has been`
  line `revised or not, be reckoned to commence on the day in which the original proceedings were signed by the`
  line `presiding officer, or in the case of a Summary Assam Rifles Court, by the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a person subject to this Act is sentenced by an Assam Rifles Court to a term of`
  line `imprisonment, not being an imprisonment in default of payment of fine, the period spent by him in civil`
  line `or Force custody during investigation, inquiry or trial of the same case, and before the date of order, such`
  line `sentence shall be set off against the term of imprisonment imposed upon him and the liability of such`
  line `person or officer to undergo imprisonment on such order of sentence shall be restricted to the remainder,`
  line `if any, of the term of imprisonment imposed upon him.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (7015)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7015&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any sentence of imprisonment is`
  line `passed under this Act by an Assam Rifles Court or whenever any sentence of death is commuted to`
  line `imprisonment, the confirming officer or in case of a Summary Assam Rifles Court, the officer holding the`
  line `Court or such other officer as may be prescribed, shall, save as otherwise provided in sub-sections (3) and`
  line `(4) direct that the sentence shall be carried out by confinement in a civil prison.`
  line
  line `(2) When a direction has been made under sub-section (1), the Commandant of the person under`
  line `sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed shall forward a warrant in the prescribed form to the`
  line `officer in charge of the prison in which such person is to be confined and shall arrange for his despatch to`
  line `such prison with the warrant.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of a sentence of imprisonment for a period not exceeding three months and passed`
  line `under this Act by an Assam Rifles Court the appropriate officer under sub-section (1) may direct that the`
  line `sentence shall be carried out by confinement in force custody instead of in a civil prison.`
  line
  line `(4) On active duty, a sentence of imprisonment may be carried out by confinement in such place as`
  line `the Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the person sentenced is serving or any prescribed`
  line `officer may from time to time appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (7016)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Temporary custody of offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7016&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence of imprisonment is directed to be`
  line `undergone in a civil prison, the offender may be kept in Force custody or in any other fit place till such`
  line `time as it is possible to send him to a civil prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (7017)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7017&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, in the opinion of an`
  line `officer not below the rank of Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the trial is held, any`
  line `sentence or portion of a sentence of imprisonment cannot for special reasons, conveniently be carried out in Force custody in accordance with the provisions of section 143, such officer may direct that such`
  line `sentence or portion of sentence shall be carried out by confinement in any civil prison or other fit place.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (7018)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Conveyance of prisoner form place to place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7018&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `A person under sentence of imprisonment may,`
  line `during his conveyance from place to place, or when on board ship, aircraft or otherwise, be subjected to`
  line `such restraint as is necessary for his safe conduct and removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (7019)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Communication of certain orders to prison officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7019&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `When an order is duly made under this`
  line `Act setting aside or varying any sentence, order or warrant under which any person is confined in a civil`
  line `prison, a warrant in accordance with such order shall be forwarded by the officer making the order or his`
  line `staff officer or such other person as may be prescribed, to the officer in charge of the prison in which such`
  line `person is confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (7020)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Execution of sentence of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7020&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `When a sentence of fine is imposed by an Assam Rifles Court`
  line `under section 55, a copy of such sentence signed and certified by the confirming officer, or where no`
  line `confirmation is required by the officer holding the trial may be sent to any Magistrate in India and such`
  line `Magistrate shall thereupon cause the fine to be recovered in accordance with the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) as if it were a sentence of fine imposed by such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (7021)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Informality or error in order or warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7021&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is sentenced to`
  line `imprisonment under this Act and is undergoing the sentence in any place or manner in which he might be`
  line `confined under a lawful order or warrant in pursuance of this Act, the confinement of such person shall`
  line `not be deemed to be illegal only by reason of informality or error in, or as respects the order, warrant or`
  line `other document, or the authority by which, or in pursuance where of such person was brought into, or is`
  line `confined in any such place, and any such order, warrant or document may be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (7022)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Pardon and remission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7022&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `When any person subject to this Act has been convicted by an Assam`
  line `Rifles Court of any offence, the Central Government or the Director-General, or in the case of a sentence`
  line `which he could have confirmed or which did not require confirmation, an officer not below the rank of`
  line `Deputy Inspector-General within whose command such person at the time of conviction was serving or`
  line `the prescribed officer may,—`
  line
  line `(a) either with or without conditions which the person sentenced accepts, pardon the person or`
  line `remit the whole or any part of the punishment awarded; or`
  line
  line `(b) mitigate the punishment awarded; or`
  line
  line `(c) commute such punishment for any less punishment or punishments mentioned in this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) either with or without conditions which the person sentenced accepts, release the person on`
  line parole.
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (7023)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Cancellation of conditional pardon, release on parole or remission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7023&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any condition on`
  line `which a person has been pardoned or released on parole or a punishment has been remitted is, in the`
  line `opinion of the authority which granted the pardon, release or remission, not fulfilled, such authority may`
  line `cancel the pardon, release or remission, and thereupon the sentence of the Court shall be carried into`
  line `effect as if such pardon, release or remission had not been granted.`
  line
  line `(2) A person whose sentence of imprisonment is carried into effect under the provisions of subsection`
  line `(1) shall undergo only the unexpired portion of his sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (7024)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Suspension of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7024&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person subject to this Act is sentenced`
  line `by an Assam Rifles Court to imprisonment, the Central Government, the Director-General or any officer`
  line `empowered to convene a General Assam Rifles Court may suspend the sentence whether or not the`
  line `offender has already been committed to prison or to Force custody.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority or officer specified in sub-section (1) may, in the case of an offender so sentenced`
  line `direct that until the order of such authority or officer have been obtained, the offender shall not be`
  line `committed to prison or to Force custody.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers conferred by sub-sections (1) and (2) may be exercised in the case of any such`
  line `sentence with has been confirmed, reduced or commuted.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (7025)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Orders pending suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7025&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where sentence referred to in section 152 is imposed by an`
  line `Assam Rifles Court other than Summary Assam Rifles Court, the confirming officer may, when`
  line `confirming the sentence, direct that the offender be not committed to prison or to Force custody until the`
  line `orders of the authority or officer specified in section 152 have been obtained.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a sentence of imprisonment is imposed by a Summary Assam Rifles Court, the officer`
  line `holding the trial or the officer authorised to approve the sentence under sub-section (2) of section 136`
  line `may make the direction referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (7026)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Release on suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7026&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence is suspended under section 152 the offender shall`
  line `forthwith be released from custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (7027)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Computation of period of suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7027&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Any period during which the sentence is under`
  line `suspension shall be reckoned as part of the term of such sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (7028)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Order after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7028&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The authority or officer specified in section 152 may, at any time`
  line `while a sentence is suspended, order—`
  line
  line `(a) that the offender be committed to undergo the unexpired portion of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the sentence be remitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (7029)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Reconsideration of case after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7029&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a sentence has been suspended, the case`
  line `may at any time, and shall at intervals of not more than four months, be reconsidered by the authority or`
  line `officer specified in section 152 or by any officer not below the rank of a Deputy Inspector-General duly`
  line `authorised by the authority or officer specified in section 152.`
  line
  line `(2) Where on such reconsideration by the officer so authorised it appears to him that the conduct of`
  line `offender since his conviction has been such as to justify a remission of the sentence, he shall refer the`
  line `matter to the authority or officer specified in section 150.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (7030)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Fresh sentence after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7030&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Where an offender, while a sentence on him is suspended`
  line `under this Act, is sentenced for any other offence, then,`
  line
  line `(a) if the further sentence is also suspended under this Act, the two sentence shall run`
  line concurrently;
  line
  line `(b) if the further sentence is for a period of three months or more and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall be so committed to prison or to Force custody for the unexpired portion of the`
  line `previous sentence, but both sentences shall run concurrently; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the further sentence is for a period of less than three months and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall be so committed on that sentence only, and the previous sentence shall, subject`
  line `to any order which may be passed under section 156 or section 157, continue to be suspended.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (7031)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Scope of power of suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7031&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `The powers conferred by sections 152 and 156 shall be in`
  line `addition to, and not in derogation of the power of mitigation, remission and commutation.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (7032)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Effect of suspension and remission on dismissal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7032&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in addition to any other sentence`
  line `the punishment of dismissal or removal has been awarded by an Assam Rifles Court, and such sentence is`
  line `suspended under section 152, then, such dismissal or removal shall not take effect until so ordered by the`
  line `authority or officer specified in section 152.`
  line
  line `(2) If such other sentence is remitted under section 156, the punishment of dismissal or removal shall`
  line `also be remitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (7033)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Disposal of property of the members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7033&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or any other`
  line `authority empowered in this behalf by that Government may, by a general or special order, make`
  line `provisions for the disposal of the private or regimental property of any person subject to this Act or anyother dues including provident fund of that person, who dies or deserts, or is ascertained to be of unsound`
  line `mind or while on active duty is officially reported as missing.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (7034)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Powers and duties conferrable and imposable on members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7034&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct that, subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations, and within the local limits of such area adjoining the border of India, as may`
  line `be specified in the order, any member of the Force may,—`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of prevention of any offence punishable under the Passport (Entry into India)`
  line `Act, 1920 (34 of 1920), the Registration of Foreigners Act 1939 (16 of 1939), the Central Excise Act,`
  line `1944 (1 of 1944), the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946), the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), the`
  line `Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967) or the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) or of`
  line `any cognizable offence punishable under any other Central Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of apprehending any person who has committed any offence referred to in`
  line `clause (a),`
  line
  line `exercise or discharge such of the powers or duties under that Act or any other Central Act as may be`
  line `specified in the said order, being the powers and duties which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `an officer of the corresponding or lower rank is by that or such other Act empowered to exercise or`
  line `discharge for the said purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, confer`
  line `or impose, with the concurrence of the State Government concerned, any of the powers or duties which`
  line `may be exercised or discharged under a State Act by a police officer upon a members of the Force who, in`
  line `the opinion of the Central Government, holds a corresponding or higher rank.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (7035)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Protection for acts of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7035&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provision of section 125 of the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) shall apply to such members of the Force who exercise or discharge any`
  line `power or duty under sub-section (1) of section 162 or on whom any power is conferred or duty is imposed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of that section in the same manner as it apply to a police officer.`
  line
  line `(2) In any suit or proceeding against any member of the Force for any act done by him in pursuance`
  line `of a warrant or order of a competent authority, it shall be lawful for him to plead, that such act was done`
  line `by him under the authority of such warrant or order.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such plea may be proved by the production of the warrant or order directing the act, and if it`
  line `is so proved the members of the Force shall thereupon be discharged from liability in respect of the act so`
  line `done by him, notwithstanding any defect in jurisdiction of the authority which issued such warrant or`
  line order.
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any legal`
  line `proceeding (whether civil or criminal) which may lawfully be brought against any member of the Force`
  line `for anything done or intended to be done under the powers conferred by, or in pursuance of, any provision`
  line `of this Act or the rules, shall be commenced within three months after the act complained of was`
  line `committed and not otherwise, and notice in writing of such proceedings and of the cause thereof shall be`
  line `given to the defendant or his superior officer at least one month before the commencement of such`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (7036)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Power of Central Government to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7036&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be`
  line `necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (7037)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7037&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for the`
  line `purposes of carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of re-constitution of the Force and the conditions of service of the members of the`
  line `Force under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the mode of enrolment and the procedure for enrolment under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the authority whose previous permission in writing is required for resigning from appointment`
  line `or withdrawing from all or any of the duties under section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) rank or ranks of an officer or a subordinate officer referred to under sub-section (2) of section`
  line 11;
  line
  line `(e) the authority who shall give previous sanction in writing under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) nature of communication or publication under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(g) other purposes of meeting or demonstration under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) form of enrolment under section 31;`
  line
  line `(i) any other purpose under clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(j) the officer who may direct that an enrolled person who has been sentenced to dismissal or`
  line `imprisonment whether combined with dismissal or not may be retained to serve in the ranks under`
  line `section 60;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of proceedings against a person and the extent of awarding punishment under`
  line `section 62;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of proceeding against an officer below the rank of a Deputy Commandant and of`
  line `the rank of subordinate officer and of the rank of Warrant Officer under sub-section (1) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of forwarding certified true copies of the proceedings and the superior authority`
  line `to whom such copies shall be forwarded under sub-section (2) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of proceeding against an officer below the rank of Commandant and of any rank`
  line `of subordinate officer and of the rank of Warrant Officer under sub-section (1) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of proceeding against any subordinate officer or a Warrant Officer under section`
  line 66;
  line
  line `(p) the officer by whose order any sum is required to be paid, for the maintenance of wife or`
  line `legitimate or illegitimate child of a person subject to this Act other than an officer, under clause (i) of`
  line `section 69;`
  line
  line `(q) the officer who may direct that the whole or any part of the pay and allowances of person`
  line `subject to this Act shall be withheld under section 71;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner and the extent of remission of deductions from pay and allowances authorised by`
  line `this Act and the authority by which such remission shall be made under section 75;`
  line
  line `(s) the authorities by whom proper provision to be made out of the pay and allowances of all`
  line `persons subject to this Act, being prisoners of war, for the dependents of such persons under section`
  line 76;
  line
  line `(t) the authorities who shall make proper provision out of the pay and allowances of any person`
  line `subject to this Act, who is prisoner of war or is missing under section 77;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner in which and the period for which any person subject to this Act may be taken into`
  line `and detained in force custody under sub-section (4) of section 80;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of making special report giving reasons for delay under section 81;`
  line
  line `(w) the authority to appoint, and the manner of appointment of, a court of inquiry; the manner of`
  line `administering oath or affirmation by such court of inquiry and the manner of making record under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 84;`
  line
  line `(x) the officer who may appoint Force police under sub-section (1) of section 85;`
  line
  line `(y) the other officer having the discretion to decide before which court the proceeding shall be`
  line `instituted under section 102;`
  line
  line `(z) the manner of filling up the vacancy of member by another officer under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 106;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of administering oath or affirmation to every member of an Assam Rifles Court`
  line `and to the Law Officer, or, as the case may be, the officer approved under section 105 before the`
  line `commencement of the trial, under sub-section (1) of section 107;`
  line
  line `(zb) the form for being duly sworn or affirmed under sub-section (2) of section 107;`
  line
  line `(zc) the officer by whom the letter, return or other documents purported to be signed shall be the`
  line `evidence of the facts stated in such letter, return or other document under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 118;
  line
  line `(zd) the other matters to be further inquired and recoded under sub-section (1) of section 120;`
  line
  line `(ze) the other matters to be recorded under sub-section (3) of section 120;`
  line
  line `(zf) the manner of keeping in custody of the accused person under sub-section (4) of section 121;`
  line
  line `(zg) the officer who may take steps to have certain persons tried under section 122;`
  line
  line `(zh) the authority for issuing certificate in case of detention in any other place under clause (b) of`
  line `section 122;`
  line
  line `(zi) the officer to whom the proceedings of every summary Assam Rifles Courts shall be`
  line `forwarded under section 137;`
  line
  line `(zj) the officer superior in command, to the one who confirmed the findings or sentence referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2) of section 139, to whom petition may be presented under that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(zk) the officer who may annul the proceeding of any Assam Rifles Court under section 140;`
  line
  line `(zl) the other officer who shall direct that sentence shall be carried out by the confinement in a`
  line `civil prison under sub-section (1) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(zm) the officer who shall forward a warrant and the form of such warrant under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 143;`
  line
  line `(zn) the officer who may from time to time appoint the place of confinement under sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(zo) the other person by whom the warrant shall be forwarded to the officer in charge of the`
  line `prison under section 147;`
  line
  line `(zp) the officer who may pardon or exercise other powers as specified under clauses (a) to (c) of`
  line `section 150;`
  line
  line `(zq) any other matter which is to be, may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to be,`
  line `or may be, made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (7038)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7038&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `The Director-General may make regulations for all or any of the`
  line `purposes of this Act other than those specified in section 165, subject to approval of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (7039)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7039&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `Every rule or regulation made under`
  line `this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in`
  line `session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session, or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (7040)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902&sectionId=7040&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00025_200647_1517807326902
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Assam Rifles Act, 1941 (5 of 1941) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Assam Rifles in existence at the commencement of this Act and constituted under the Act`
  line `so repealed shall be deemed to be reconstituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) members of the Assam Rifles in existence at the commencement of this Act and appointed`
  line `under the Act so repealed shall be deemed to have been appointed or, as the case may be, enrolled as`
  line `such under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any appeal, application, trial, inquiry or investigation pending immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be disposed of, continued, held or made, as the case may be, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Assam Rifles Act, 1941 (5 of 1941), as if this Act had not come`
  line `into force;`
  line
  line `(d) any thing done or any action taken before the commencement of this Act, in relation to any`
  line `person appointed or enrolled, shall be valid and as effective in law as if such thing or action was done`
  line `or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
